title: 2008 Orthophotography
description: Peoria County contracted with the The Sanborn Map Company to receive aerial imagery during spring leaf-off in 2008.? The aerial imagery covers the Peoria County boundary extent with resolutions of one foot in rural areas and six inches in the Peoria metro area.? The data is available for download in zip file format.? The zip file contains aerial imagery in a MrSID compressed format per township boundary area extent, one county-wide aerial mosaic in MrSID format, and a shapefile of township boundaries.? The shapefile of township boundaries was used to create the MrSID aerials by township boundary area extent.? The zip file is 9.3 GB in size and can be downloaded by clicking?Here.Additional MetadataDigital Photo Scale:??1 = 833' for the urban project area?.1 = 1667' for the rural project area.Alternate: 1 = 833' for the entire project area.Project Size:? 629 plus the 750ft buffer area.Sun Angle:? Greater than 30 degrees above the horizon.Spacing:? Full stereoscopic coverage.Endlap:? 60 percent, 80 percent in commercial areas.Sidelap:? 30 percent, 60 percent in commercial areas.Crab:? Less than 3 degrees between and within any photo.Tilt:? Less than 3% any photo, less than 5% between photos.Flight Height Above Ground:? 3,900'.Image Type:? Color and Color IR.The aerial imagery is bound to the? title: Damage Points
description: Two tornadoes were spotted in Peoria County, Illinois on March 15, 2016.  One tornado was an EF-2 and had a damage path of 7.6 miles.  The second tornado was an EF-0 with a damage path of 3.83 miles.  Numerous structures and trees were damaged from this super cell storm.  This map displays the tornado paths and damage locations.

title: 2003 Orthophotography
description: Peoria County contracted with the Surdex Corporation to receive aerial imagery during spring leaf-off in 2003.? The aerial imagery covers the Peoria County boundary extent with resolutions of one foot in rural areas and six inches in the Peoria metro area.? The data is available for download in zip file format.? The zip file contains aerial imagery in a MrSID compressed format.? Each MrSID image covers an extent of a township boundary in Peoria County.? Higher quality imagery in TIF format is available upon request.? The delivery areas of the TIF imagery are in shapefile format and can be found in the zip file.? The zip file is 6 GB in size and can be downloaded by clicking?Here.The aerial imagery is bound to the? Peoria County GIS Open Data License Agreement which can be found here:??https://data-peoriacountygis.opendata.arcgis.com/pages/peoria-county-gis-open-data-license-agreement.

title: LIDAR Data
description: This zip file contains LIDAR, Digital Terrain Models (DTM's), surface, and breakline datasets covering the extent of Peoria County.? The LIDAR data was captured during spring leaf-off in 2008.? There are eight databases in Esri's file geodatabase format which are broken down by eight areas in the County.? The DTM's conform to the ASPRS Class I Standards using the Illinois State Plane West coordinate system.More recent LIDAR data for Peoria County, IL was captured in 2012 by the State of Illinois through the Illinois Height Modernization Program (ILHMP).? Please click?Here?to read about the program and data available for download.This data is bound to the Peoria County GIS Open Data License Agreement which can be found here:??https://data-peoriacountygis.opendata.arcgis.com/pages/peoria-county-gis-open-data-license-agreement.
